Exception:
  Error occures while the excecution of the program.

syntax error can't handle in exception handling.

index error===>out of range of index
nameerror===>variable not defined
type error===>when concatenate two different types of datatype
indendation error==>occurs when not giving correct space

intrepreter:will find these below error
#syntax error
#indentation error
these above two errors are not handle by exception handling

a=10
b=0
print(a/b) #zero division error

a='program'
b=10
print(a+b) #type error

l=[1,2]
l.append(3)
print(l) #no error

output:
  Traceback (most recent call last):
    File "C:\Users\matha\PycharmProjects\Test\140_.py", line 218, in <module>
      print(a/b) #zero division error
            ~^~
  ZeroDivisionError: division by zero

#tightly coupled system:
  #while the execution of program if error occurs at particular line it will stop and not execute the another line if its correct.

#loosly coupled system: micro service
  how to avoid exception:
    By using try,except :
  try:
    a=10
    b=0
    print(a/b) #zero division error
  except:
    print('Exception in division part')
  try:
    a='program'
    b=10
    print(a+b) #type error
  except:
    print('exception in + operation')
  try:
    l=[1,2]
    l.append(3)
    print(l) #no error
  except:
    print('Exception in append opeartion')
  
  output:
    Exception in division part
    exception in + operation
    [1, 2, 3]

try and except is the pair .if try used then except is also used

 try:
    l=[1,2]
    l.append(3)
    print(l) #no error
  except Exception as e:
    print('Exception in append opeartion')
    print(Exception) # class
    print(e) #error definition
    print(type(e)) #type of the error
  else:#no exception -->it will works
    print('No exception')
  finally:#with exception or without exception it will work
    print('try,execept finished')

##how to handle specific exception:
  try:
    a='program'
    b=10
    print(a+b) #type error
  except TypeError:
    print('exception in + operation')
  output:
  exception in + operation

#handling two errors at same time
  try:
      print(10/0) #zerodivision error
      a='program'
      b=10
      print(a+b) #type error
  except (TypeError,ZeroDivisionError): #only handle these two errors only
      print('exception in + operation')

  output:exception in + operation







